Babafemi Ojudu, a presidential adviser, has said that he will go back to farming if President Muhammadu Buhari chooses Bola Tinubu, National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, as his presidential candidate for 2023.Buhari’s Special Adviser on Political Matters said this during an interview with Chude Jideonwo. Babafemi Ojudu



When asked if he would fall in line if President Buhari chooses Tinubu as his candidate, Ojudu said he would never.Ojudu claimed he can never support or work with someone he does not believe in.He said, “Never. I’ll never support it. Write it down. I’ll go back to the farm. If I don’t believe in you, I’ll not work with you or for you.”Meanwhile, Ojudu had earlier clarified that he would not support Tinubu’s presidential ambition due to his “principled political choices”, not betrayal.